OL,3,C'It is daunting': Parents say children
OL,4,Cwith autism have limited childhoods
OL,6,FParents of autistic children in say
OL,7,Fthey are getting trapped in poverty as
OL,8,Fthey are unable to work full-time due
OL,9,Fto caring obligations.
OL,11,FThe issue is exacerbated by a lack of
OL,12,Fschool holiday activities for
OL,13,Fneurodivergent children, the parents
OL,14,Fsay.
OL,16,FSome describe their experiences as
OL,17,F"daunting", adding their children are
OL,18,Fleft with childhoods resembling
OL,19,F"lockdown."
