OL,3,C'It is daunting': Parents say children
OL,4,Cwith autism have limited childhoods
OL,6,F"She does require that structure,
OL,7,Fgetting up in the morning and knowing
OL,8,Fwe have a planned activity even if
OL,9,Fit's just for a couple of hours, can
OL,10,Fmean the world of difference to her
OL,11,Fmood, well-being and for us as a
OL,12,Ffamily as well."
OL,14,FLorna Higgins-Bare says she had to
OL,15,Fleave a full-time job in business for
OL,16,Fa different role when her son was
OL,17,Fdiagnosed with autism - a move that
OL,18,Fhas added strain to her and her
OL,19,Ffamily's lives.
