OL,3,C'It is daunting': Parents say children
OL,4,Cwith autism have limited childhoods
OL,6,FShe explained: "Due to the lack of
OL,7,Fsupport for my son, I wouldn't have
OL,8,Fbeen able to go back to work full-time
OL,9,Fand I certainly wouldn't have been
OL,10,Fable to go back to the role that I was
OL,11,Fqualified and trained in.
OL,13,F"Working term-time and part-time means
OL,14,Fthat financially I am in no better
OL,15,Fposition if anything I am actually a
OL,16,Flot worse off because I can't find
OL,17,Fchildcare for my son.
OL,19,F"His needs aren't being met outside of
OL,20,Fschool times so it's pushed me into
OL,21,Falmost a type of middle-class poverty."
